ğŸŒ€ Step 4: Side Effects Run (after first paint)
4.1 useEffect from useContent
useEffect(() => {
  refresh();
  let interval = setInterval(() => refresh(), 10000);
  return () => clearInterval(interval);
}, [])


Runs right after first render.

Calls refresh() immediately â†’ makes an API call to backend.

Starts a 10s interval to call refresh() repeatedly.

4.2 useEffect from Dashbord
useEffect(() => {
  refresh();
}, [modelOpen])


Also runs right after first render (because every effect runs once after mount).

Calls refresh() again.

âš¡ This means your first mount triggers two API calls (one from useContent, one from Dashbord).

