                                               // IMP 
                       In React:

First â†’ React runs the component function (Dashbord in your case).

This builds the UI tree (JSX â†’ virtual DOM).

Then â†’ React paints it on screen.

After that â†’ useEffect runs.

ğŸ‘‰ Thatâ€™s why we say:
useEffect runs after the first render (mount), not during render.

So in your case:

Dashbord() runs â†’ React sees useEffect(() => { refresh(); }, [modelOpen]).

It schedules that effect to run after the paint.

Once the UI is visible, React runs refresh().

That makes the API call, updates contents, and re-renders.

